    <description pref="false" type="">
                                <text>Represents a popular episode in the 10th-century “Ise Monogatari” (The Tales of Ise) series of poems on love and journeying; in this episode, a young aristocrat comes to a place called Eight Bridges (Yatsuhashi) where a river branched into eight channels, each spanned by a bridge. He writes a poem of five lines about irises growing there. The poem expresses his longing for his wife left behind in the capital city.
[Source: Metropolitan Museum of Art online. www.metmuseum.org  Page: accessed 22 October 2006.]</text>
                                <author>
                                    <name refid="131347215" type="corporate" vocab="viaf">Visual Resources Association</name>
